A police officer died following a road accident involving two lorries, a van and a school bus at Toll trading centre in Juja on Saturday. The officer, attached to Government Check Unit (GVCU), died while undergoing treatment at the Thika Level 5 hospital. Three students of Limuru Girlsâ€™ High school were seriously injured in the Thika Superhighway accident. Witnesses said officers from the GVCU had stopped the van and the school bus belonging to Dagoretti High School for inspection. The driver of a lorry carrying wheat lost control of the car and rammed the van which hit another lorry ferrying sand. The police officer was talking with the van driver when he was caught in between the two vehicles. The driver of the lorry sustained cuts on his head. No one in the other two vehicles was injured. Click here for the latest political news